<item>
            <title>[LU-13299] LNet: add the option to reset statistics to lnetctl utility</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13299</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently the only command option for &quot;lnetctl stats&quot; is &quot;show&quot;. At least when debugging connectivity issues, it would be useful to be able to clean up the stats by executing, for instance, &quot;lnetctl stats reset&quot;, as it would be easier to detect the changes in stats from the clean state rather than on top of historical values.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="58194">LU-13299</key>
